jobs_results.title: Head - Delivery & Solution Architect
jobs_results.description:
The Offer
• Exciting opportunity to join a leading media brand
• A senior role with immense scope of performing and driving results
• Lead a team of talented professionals

The Job

You will be reporting to the Head of Engineering and will be leading the Tech team. Your responsibilities include:
• Architecting, developing and deploying secure and scalable systems, involving multiple technologies and integration with existing systems.
• Driving long-term vision by collaborating with senior managers to determine business-specific application needs.
• Working with project and program leads from each business unit to ensure they understand the objectives for joint strategic efforts.
• Compiling and implementing application development plans for new or existing applications.
• Supervising design, testing, and modification stages, running diagnostic tests and performing debugging procedures.
• Demonstrating application prototypes and integrating user feedback.
• Performing application... integration, maintenance, upgrades and migration.
• Ensuring proper documentation is in place along with the team's compliance with engineering disciplines, policies, procedures and standards.
• Maintaining creativity and innovation by staying on top of industry, technological trends and integrating these trends in application architecture.
• Mentoring engineers and working with them to remove roadblocks.

The Profile
• You possess a good university degree in Software or Computer Engineering, Computer Science, Technology or equivalent.
• You have at least 8 years' relevant working experience developing applications, systems using latest technologies.
• Extensive experience with solution architecture and engineering of complex and highly scalable applications using Agile methodologies, is required.
• Proficiency in programming languages, such as PHP and .NET, JavaScript, Python is a must.
• Prior experience within project management using Agile and waterfall methodologies would be preferred.
• You have extensive experience in aligning application development with business needs using MVC, Cloud (AWS, GCP, Azure), SaaS, Paas, SQL, Low Code, Microservice/container, REST API, Serverless, n-tier architecture and Databases (MySQL, Oracle, MS SQL).
• Exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills along with great leadership and interpersonal skills are required to succeed in this role.
• You possess excellent organizational and time management skills along with great collaboration and communication skills.
• You have a good understanding of technologies, data and digital trends, especially in the media-related industry. Ad-tech, Martech experience is advantageous.
• You have the ability to define clear solutions in collaboration with different teams and stakeholders.
• You also possess a good track record of following engineering best-practices and successfully designing and delivering innovations and technology solutions.

The Employer

Our client is an established media firm. With headlines across a wide range of topics, their publications attract millions of viewers on a daily basis

jobs_results.title: Google Cloud Solution Architect (Specialist-Manager)
jobs_results.description:
About Accenture

Accenture is a global professional services company with leading capabilities in digital, cloud and security. Combining unmatched experience and specialized skills across more than 40 industries, we offer Strategy and Consulting, Interactive, Technology and Operations services—all powered by the world’s largest network of Advanced Technology and Intelligent Operations centres. Our 506,000 people deliver on the promise of technology and human ingenuity every day, serving clients in more than 120 countries. We embrace the power of change to create value and shared success for our clients, people, shareholders, partners and communities. Visit us at www.accenture.com.

Accenture Technology combines business and industry insights with innovative technology services to transform your business. Join one of the world’s largest independent providers of technology services to grow your expertise and help clients worldwide to innovate at scale and transform their businesses... Help change how the world works and lives through technology innovation.

Job Title: Google Cloud Solution Architect (Specialist-Manager level)

Accenture's Google Cloud Platform team helps customers transform and evolve their business through the use of Google’s global network, web-scale data centers and software infrastructure. You will be an integral member in our entrepreneurial team in this rapidly growing business, helping to shape the future of businesses of all sizes use technology to connect with key stakeholders across all levels.

Responsibilities include and are not limited to:
• Serve as the Google Cloud Platform (GCP) SME to clients within Accenture team engagements for design, architecture, and deployment in the GCP cloud space using automated orchestration and configuration management techniques
• Perform as a partner with leading Cloud Service Provider (CSPs) and enterprises to meet security goals and pave the way for digital transformation and modernization
• Partner clients and team members to identify the right balance of defense-in-depth techniques to translate customer’s goals into a secure and effective solution
• Engage in designing and implementing secure and compliant enterprise servers, network infrastructure, boundary protection, and cloud architectures using Infrastructure-as-Code
• Be exposed to a myriad of other technology stacks in the leading cloud providers such as GCP, Azure and AWS understanding and utilizing their unique native services in deployments
• Authoring and peer review of detailed design documentation, including security documentation and inclusive of vendor best practices

Critical Success Factors
• Minimum 1 Professional certification in GCP
• Minimum 2-8 years of experience in GCP

You will also have opportunities to hone your functional skills and expertise in an area of specialization. We offer a variety of formal and informal training programs at every level to help you acquire and build specialized skills faster. Learning takes place both on the job and through formal training conducted online, in the classroom, or in collaboration with teammates. The sheer variety of work we do, and the experience it offers, provide an unbeatable platform from which to build a career.

Accenture is an equal opportunities employer and welcomes applications from all sections of society and does not discriminate on grounds of race, religion or belief, ethnic or national origin, disability, age, citizenship, marital, domestic or civil partnership status, sexual orientation, gender identity, or any other basis as protected by applicable law
